                                approx. <geo>52.475399, -7.445995</geo>.
                            </origPlace>
                            <origDate><!--?? century A.D--></origDate>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance type="found" notAfter="1858"><p>Found by a labourer digging in a field in the parish of Killamery in the Summer of 1858. It is not clear if the brooch is associated with the monastic site.                           
                            <q>Of the <ref target="https://monasticon.celt.dias.ie/showrecord.php?id=1799">monastic site</ref> only a high cross (KK030-008004-), two cross-slabs (KK030-008005-; KK030-008011-), a stone cross (KK030-008013-), the remains of a church (KK030-008003-) and two bullaun stones (KK030-008006-; KK030-008008-) are currently visible at the location</q> (<ref source="https://maps.archaeology.ie/HistoricEnvironment/?SMRS=KK030-008005-">Archaeology.ie</ref>).</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed">National Museum of Ireland
                        </provenance>
