            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p> '[the possession] of Cíarodur son of [?]'</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary"> 
                <list type="witDetail">
                    <item n="1"><p>As pointed out by <ref source="#WHI1992">Okasha (1992, 59)</ref> <q>Ciarodur is a recorded masculine Old Irish personal name, here probably in the genitive (<ref source="#OBR1962">O'Brien 1962, 545 and 418</ref>, the latter quoting a form in the genitive)</q>. It is a compound of <ref target="https://dil.ie/9011"><hi rend="italic">cíar</hi></ref> 'dark, black' and <ref target="https://dil.ie/33495"><hi rend="italic">odur</hi></ref> 'dun, greyish brown'.</p></item>
                </list>
